{
  "text": "We instead use a correspondence checking scheme where the auxiliary view is omitted, and the approximating ellipses of the regions are compared using their epipolar tangents [CITATION_1] . The fundamental matrix F, relates corresponding points x and x ′ in the two views as x T Fx ′ = 0 [CITATION_2] . First we extract the epipoles of the fundamental matrix F, as the left and right singular vectors. Using these, and the pole-polar relationship [CITATION_3] , we then compute the two points ",
